text: Edward Reynolds was an English Anglican priest in the 17th century.Historic England The son of Bishop Edward Reynolds, Geni he was educated at Magdalen College, Oxford.Alumni Oxonienses 1500-1714, Rabbetts-Rhodes He became the Rector of St Peter's Church, Northampton. He was Archdeacon of Norfolk from 1661 until his death on 28 June, 1698. ==Notes== Category:17th-century English Anglican priests Category:Archdeacons of Norfolk Category:Alumni of Magdalen College, Oxford Category:1698 deaths
title: Edward Reynolds (priest)
